This project implements a feedforward neural network to classify handwritten digits 0 and 1 using a subset of the MNIST dataset.

Model
Input: 20×20 images (flattened to 400 features)
Architecture:
Dense (25 units, sigmoid)
Dense (15 units, sigmoid)
Dense (1 unit, sigmoid)
Loss: Binary Crossentropy
Optimizer: Adam
Implementation
Built using TensorFlow/Keras for training and prediction
Also includes a NumPy implementation of forward propagation to demonstrate how dense layers work internally
Output
Model predicts a probability:
≥ 0.5 → digit 1
< 0.5 → digit 0
Results
Training loss decreases over epochs
Model achieves high accuracy for binary classification
NumPy and TensorFlow implementations give consistent predictions
Key Idea

This project shows both:

Practical neural network training using a framework
Mathematical implementation of neural networks from scratch
